DOCUMENT();

#image scale
$imgScale = .2;

#image aspect ratio
$width = $imgScale*1443;
$height = $imgScale*2126;

loadMacros(   
	"PGstandard.pl",     # Standard macros for PG language
	"MathObjects.pl",
	"PGML.pl",
	"parserPopUp.pl",
	"parserMultiAnswer.pl",
	"parserRadioButtons.pl",
	#"source.pl",        # allows code to be displayed on certain sites.
	#"PGcourse.pl", 	 # Customization file for the course
   	);

TEXT(beginproblem());

##############################################################
#
#  Setup
#
#

Context("Numeric");
#given
$VV= random(10,15,1); #[m/s]
$RR= random(.3,0.6,0.1); #[m]

#computation
$Ans = 2*999*$VV**2*$RR*0.03; #[N]

#set tolerance
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>.01,);

##############################################################
#
#  PGML 
#
#

BEGIN_PGML

[@ image("UBC-FLU-18-061.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

Water flows through a semi-circular nozzle as shown in the figure. Find the [`y`]-component of the force [`R_y`] required to hold the nozzle if the circle has a radius [`R=[$RR]`] [`m`] and outflow velocity [`V=[$VV]`] [`m/s`]. [`\rho_{H_2O}=999`] [`kg/m^3`].

[`R_y=`] [____]{"$Ans"} [`N`]

END_PGML

